# Prompting BI blog rules

Astro 5 static blog deployed to GitHub Pages at https://promptingbi.com. Content lives in `src/content/blog/` as markdown. Every push to `main` auto-deploys via GitHub Actions; a daily scheduled build also publishes future-dated posts when their date arrives.

## Creating a new post

Preferred: run `npm run new-post "My Post Title"` (scaffolds file + image folder). Or create `src/content/blog/<slug>.md` with EXACTLY this front matter shape:

```markdown
---
title: "Post Title Here"
date: 2026-07-20T09:00:00Z
permalink: "2026/07/20/post-slug-here"
description: "One-sentence teaser. Shown on homepage, RSS, and meta description."
featured: /images/2026/07/some-image.png   # optional
draft: true                                 # flip to false to publish
---
```

Rules:
- `permalink` must be `YYYY/MM/DD/slug` matching the date — preserves the WordPress-era URL structure
- `date` must be ISO with Z suffix; future dates publish automatically on the daily build
- `draft: true` posts never build; remove or set false to publish
- slug = kebab-case; `description` under 160 characters

## Images

- Store in `public/images/YYYY/MM/` (mirror the post date)
- Reference as `/images/YYYY/MM/name.png` (absolute path, no `public/` prefix)
- Always include descriptive alt text

## Voice and style

- Author: Tommy Puglia, BI consultant (Power BI / Microsoft Fabric / AI). First person, conversational, practical, opinionated but friendly
- Posts teach through worked examples with screenshots, then end with a short "Takeaways" bullet list
- Audience: Power BI / Fabric professionals learning to use generative AI well

## Do not

- Do not edit `public/CNAME`, the `site` URL in `astro.config.mjs`, or `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` unless explicitly asked
- Do not change permalinks of existing posts (breaks inbound links)
- Do not add npm dependencies without asking
